<DOC><DOCNO> AP891216-0137 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-16-89 1911EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Hungary-Kohl     12-16 0230</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Hungary-Kohl,0237</SECOND><HEAD>Kohl Praises Hungary for Leading Role in East European Reforms</HEAD><DATELINE>BUDAPEST, Hungary (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Visiting Chancellor Helmut Kohl of WestGermany praised Hungary on Saturday for leading the reformssweeping Eastern Europe and said it ``knocked the first stone'' outof the Berlin Wall.   Kohl, who arrived earlier in the day for an official three-dayvisit, thanked Hungary as he received an honorary doctorate atEoetvoes Lorand University.   ``Hungary knocked the first stone from the Wall,'' Kohl said,referring to the decision to open Hungarian borders with Austria onSept. 11.   The exodus of tens of thousands of East Germans to West Germanyvia Hungary and Austria helped spark unprecedented politicalreforms in the ruling Communist parties of East Germany and otherSoviet-bloc countries.   Kohl said that without the ``courageous decision by theHungarian government,'' the dramatic changes in East Germany wouldnot have happened _ at least not so quickly.   ``The solidarity and help of the Hungarians for the people whowere longing for freedom will not be forgotten,'' Kohl told theuniversity audience.   He promised additional West German financial aid to help Hungaryrestructure its economy and society.   Kohl's government has set aside for Hungary state-guaranteedcredits worth millions of dollars.   Kohl was welcomed at the airport by Hungarian Premier MiklosNemeth. The two held talks Saturday afternoon, and Kohl willaddress Parliament on Monday.</TEXT></DOC>